OL,6,FNarita Bahra KC, appearing for the
OL,7,Fdefence, said Wallis uses female
OL,8,Fpronouns, referring to Jamie as her
OL,9,F"deadname".
OL,11,FShe argued it was "disappointing" the
OL,12,Fcase had come to court, criticising
OL,13,FSouth Wales Police and the Crown
OL,14,FProsecution Service for not dealing
OL,15,Fwith the issue outside the court.
OL,17,FMs Bahra argued it was "unequivocal"
OL,18,Fthat Wallis had been suffering from
OL,19,Fmental health difficulties at the time
OL,20,Fof the offending, partly brought on by
OL,21,Ftheir transitioning.
